recent.name: then came clouds of smoke
recent.description:
This work is part of our series "Circular Ruins", itself stemming from "Potential Herbariums", a wide array of generative works derived from GANs. These models were trained on more than 4 million herbariums gathered worldwide. 
Inspired by a short story by Jorge Luis Borges as well as "Atlas of Remote Islands", a book by Judith Schalansky, we used the GAN-generated shapes of a fascinating -and somewhat impossible- vegetal to create a 3D landscape, a imaginary remote island to be explored. Ref. AV-2021-U-72

recent.name: Enter the Supersensorium
recent.description:
We find ourselves strolling the aisles of a vast sensorium. On the shelves is a trove of experiences: video games, movies, TV shows, virtual reality, books, and comics, all prepackaged for our consumption. What had previously been accomplished for food through the distribution of supermarkets has now been done with experience itself. The recent grand opening of this supersensorium has been mediated through the screen, a panoply of icons, images, links, downloads, and videos auto-playing, which we browse through entirely at our leisure.
-Erik Hoel

recent.name: Puzzled
recent.description:
"Puzzled" is an obscure reflection of the current times. With the uncertainty of a global pandemic, civil unrest, and financial instability, it seems the earth is a strange sticky puzzle. I attempted to express these ideas and concerns in a simple 10-second piece, but also make it something visually-attractive to watch. The visual is something hard to look away from, and so are the issues that influenced it.

Created with 3ds Max, Phoenix FD, TyFlow, and After Effects

recent.name: The Chrysanthemum and the Ξxcalibur
recent.description: This work asks about changing values in the past and the future, with the theme of the Choyo Festival, one of Japan's five festivals. In the world, new divinity is constantly scrolling. Strangely enough, this series "NΞW GAMΞ+" had started just before coronaviruses broke out. When life intersects from the micro and macro viewpoint, the existence of COVID-19 gives us great awareness, what is bug or what is normal. NΞW GAMΞ+ means that we replay it with taking over the status of cleared games. When we reconsider the new normal day and the future, we can make better actions in the real world as a player. We will be able to start on "NΞW (NORMAL) GAMΞ" many times.

recent.name: Phil Collen
recent.description: Conceived in a period of insomnia, this is an exploration of light and geometry. How do these simple shapes react to each other, and what happens as they change their perspectives? Much of my work over the last year has focused on using basic shapes as stand-ins for larger ideas. Representation without representation. This piece is named after Phil Collen, a guitarist for the band Def Leppard, which I pay tribute to in the visual style of the piece. Limitations in current NFT technology result in a highly compressed image for minting, with visual loss, but I will provide a pristine pro-res 4444 render to this piece's collector.
